Simple Past (Interrogative)

Auxiliar: Did

We had a bad day.
Did we have a bad day?

He went to jail.
Did go to jail?

You did a great job.
Did you do a great job?

They saw a cat.
Did they see a cat?

I looked at you.
Did I look at you?

You wanted more.
Did want more?

He asked if I could drive.
Did he ask if i could drive.

She tried many times.
Did she trie many times.

They stopped at a good place.
Did they stop at a good place.

It needed to be fixed.
Did it need to be fixed.
